He died at the scene which happened in the Manzana Admin Area on Wednesday. CAPE TOWN – Police on Thursday were investigating a family killing in the Eastern Cape. A man was alleged to have murdered both his wife and 14-year-old stepson before turning the gun on himself. He died at the scene which happened in the Manzana Admin Area on Wednesday. Police spokesperson Thembinkosi Kinana said: “People should seek professional help and open up about the circumstances they are facing behind these things.”